2025-09-26 16:15:49,324 - INFO - Strategy Summary: Based on the given data, the experiment with lowest deviation and variability was the third trial, which had a deviation of 9.163559 and variability of 2.496496. This trial also had the second highest aspirate speed (16 uL/s), highest dispense speed (30 uL/s), lowest aspirate wait time (4.259607 s) and retract speed (14.326069 uL/s).

Patterns observed include:

- Lower aspirate speed seems to result in lower deviation and variability. This is seen in trial 3 and 4 where lower aspirate speeds of 16 and 14 resulted in lower deviation and variability compared to other trials.
- Similarly, higher dispense speeds also seem to result in lower deviation and variability. This is seen in trial 3 where the highest dispense speed (30 uL/s) resulted in lowest deviation and variability.

